equation_narrative.headline: N-terminal hydrophobic core position resolved through structural contacts and branched-chain specificity
equation_narrative.story: Position 3 in ubiquitin sits at the N-terminus in a hydrophobic environment, surrounded by 9 structural contacts. Through layers 1-23, the model assembles a representation of this buried context, with the logit lens initially reflecting charged and polar character before shifting toward hydrophobic residues around L13. The representation remains ambiguous between branched-chain aliphatics (V, L, I) through L27, with leucine peaking at 50.7%. The decisive shift occurs at L28-33, where isoleucine-specific prediction channels activate: MLP neuron N32:1117 contributes 1.176 projection, and structural attention head L32:H18 writes 1.98 toward I. The model correctly selects isoleucine with 74.72% confidence, distinguishing it from valine (23.9%) through beta-branching specificity encoded in late-layer features.

perception_phase.summary: Layers 1-23 assemble a representation of position 3's hydrophobic burial context through structural attention. Nine structural contacts provide predominantly hydrophobic signal, though the early logit lens (L1-12) shows charged residues (S, Y, H, D, E) leading—reflecting generic N-terminal encoding rather than local chemistry. The representation shifts decisively at L13 when valine emerges (22.4%), marking the transition to hydrophobic character. By L17, the logit lens shows V (12.89%), L (10.77%), and I (6.55%) competing, consistent with the buried aliphatic environment. Attention features at L18 (F18:6149, F18:9838, F18:2648) encode structural context with projections around 18. The representation through L23 is clearly hydrophobic-leaning but ambiguous among branched-chain residues, with L (32.49%) and V (23.67%) leading I (20.42%).
perception_phase.context_character: By L23, the representation encodes a buried hydrophobic core position at the N-terminus, surrounded by aliphatic contacts. The context strongly constrains to branched-chain residues (V, L, I collectively ~76%), with minimal polar or charged character.
key_information_sources: Structural contacts: 9 residues within contact distance, predominantly hydrophobic (local sequence shows F4, V5, K6, T7, L8)
Co-evolutionary signal: 2 coupled positions detected, suggesting functional constraints beyond local packing
L13 transition: MLP neurons shift representation from charged to hydrophobic (N13:3959 writes 0.296 toward I, N13:3719 erases -0.325 from A)
L18 structural features: F18:6149 (18.72 proj), F18:9838 (18.54 proj) encode burial and secondary structure context

decision_phase.summary: The decision crystallizes at L28-33 as isoleucine-specific prediction channels activate. At L28, I overtakes L (51.1% vs 50.7%) for the first time, driven by attention writing events. Layer 32 delivers the strongest evidence: MLP neuron N32:1117 contributes 1.176 projection specifically for I, while structural attention head L32:H18 writes 1.98 by reading buried contacts. Final layer features F33:5788 (MLP, 117.27 proj) and F33:4166 (attn, 106.12 proj) are highly I-enriched prediction channels that cement the 74.72% confidence.
decision_phase.transition: The perception-to-decision boundary occurs at L23-25. At L23, the representation remains ambiguous (L 32.49%, V 23.67%, I 20.42%). By L24, amino-acid-specific prediction features emerge: F24:5827 (27.98 proj) and F24:4430 (21.6 proj) begin differentiating among hydrophobic candidates. L25 MLP neurons show strong I-specific writing (N25:83 contributes 0.481, N25:4431 contributes 0.431), marking the shift from context encoding to candidate selection.

candidates.narrative: Isoleucine emerges as the winner through late-layer specificity channels that distinguish beta-branching from other aliphatics. Starting from only 20.42% at L23, I rises steadily through L24-29 (52.31%) as prediction neurons activate. The decisive push comes at L28-33: N32:1117 contributes 1.176 projection (top MLP writer), structural attention L32:H18 writes 1.98, and final-layer feature F33:5788 (117.27 proj) acts as a highly I-specific prediction channel. I reaches 74.72% by distinguishing itself from valine through beta-branching specificity encoded in these late features.
candidates.key_layers: Overtakes L at L28, accelerates L29-33
key_evidence: N32:1117 (1.176 proj) — strongest I-specific MLP neuron, votes I > Y > A
L32:H18 (1.98 proj) — structural writer reading buried contacts with 50.3% structural attention
F33:5788 (MLP, 117.27 proj) — dominant I-specific prediction channel
N29:4251 (0.84 proj) — I-specific neuron votes I > P > F

candidates.narrative: Valine is the runner-up, peaking early at 40.1% (L19) when the representation encodes generic hydrophobic burial. V leads the logit lens from L13-L21, reflecting its compatibility with the aliphatic core context. However, V lacks the beta-branching specificity that late-layer features encode for I. V declines from 23.67% at L23 to 12.15% at L29 before recovering slightly to 23.9% final—it remains a strong alternative but loses to I's more specific structural fit.
candidates.key_layers: Peaks L19 (40.1%), declines L24-29, stabilizes at 23.9%
key_evidence: Early dominance reflects hydrophobic representation character, not model belief
Loses ground as beta-branching specificity channels activate L28+
Final 23.9% shows V remains chemically compatible but less optimal than I

candidates.narrative: Leucine is a strong contender that leads the actual decision phase from L22-L27, peaking at 50.67% (L27). L rises from 32.49% at L23 as hydrophobic-specific neurons activate (N21:4256 contributes 0.417, N22:3173 contributes 0.388). However, L collapses dramatically from 50.67% to 1.08% between L27-L33 as isoleucine-specific features dominate. The late erasure suggests L is compatible with the buried context but lacks the precise beta-branching geometry that I provides.
candidates.key_layers: Leads L22-L27, peaks at L27 (50.67%), collapses L28-33
key_evidence: N22:3173 (0.388 proj) — writes for I but also supports L and D
L27 peak reflects generic aliphatic compatibility before fine-grained discrimination
Late collapse indicates I-specific features actively suppress L in final layers

candidates.narrative: Alanine leads the logit lens at L0 (19.99%), reflecting the embedding's generic hydrophobic bias before any contextual information is processed. A declines steadily as structural contacts are read: 10.33% at L8, 2.78% at L17, and 0.07% final. This trajectory shows the representation shifting from a generic hydrophobic prior to a context-specific buried aliphatic environment that requires larger sidechains. A's early prominence is a logit-lens artifact of the embedding space, not a model belief.
key_evidence: L0 peak reflects embedding-space hydrophobic bias before context integration
Erased by structural contact reading L1-L13 as larger sidechains become favored

turning_points.description: The representation shifts from charged/polar to hydrophobic character at L13. The logit lens shows valine emerging (22.4%) as alanine fades, marking the integration of structural burial context. MLP neuron N13:3959 writes 0.296 toward I while N13:3719 erases -0.325 from A. This is the key perception-phase transition where the model moves from generic N-terminal encoding to specific hydrophobic core recognition.

Leucine takes the lead (L22: 26.9% → L23: 32.49%) as the representation becomes strongly aliphatic-specific. MLP layer 22 contributes 3.05 net projection despite mixed signals (N22:3173 writes 0.388 for I, but erasers like N22:4621 remove -0.351). This marks the final perception-phase refinement before decision channels activate, with the representation now clearly encoding 'buried branched-chain aliphatic' but not yet committing to I vs L vs V.

Isoleucine overtakes leucine at L28 (51.1% vs 50.7%) and accelerates to 74.72% through the strongest prediction channels in the network. L32 delivers decisive evidence: N32:1117 contributes 1.176 (top I-specific neuron), attention head L32:H18 writes 1.98 by reading structural contacts, and L33 features F33:5788 (117.27 proj) and F33:4166 (106.12 proj) act as highly enriched I-specific prediction channels. This is where beta-branching specificity distinguishes I from L and V.

deep_dives.label: Structural attention L1-L18
deep_dives.caption: Examine how attention heads read the 9 structural contacts to build the hydrophobic burial representation. L1 features show generic position encoding, L9 features integrate local chemistry, and L18 features encode the refined structural context that constrains to branched-chain residues.

deep_dives.label: Hydrophobic transition L12-L14
deep_dives.caption: Track the critical shift from charged/polar to hydrophobic representation. L12 shows mixed signals, L13 delivers the decisive shift (N13:3959 writes 0.296 for I, N13:3719 erases -0.325 from A), and L14 consolidates the aliphatic character.

deep_dives.label: Perception→Decision L23-L25
deep_dives.caption: See the transition from context encoding to candidate selection. L23 features encode structural context with moderate projections (~18-28). L24 features show the first amino-acid-specific prediction channels emerging (F24:5827 at 27.98 proj, F24:4430 at 21.6 proj).

deep_dives.label: MLP decision L29-L32
deep_dives.caption: The decisive MLP push for isoleucine. L29 N29:4251 contributes 0.84 (I > P > F), L30 shows mixed signals, L31 N31:3170 writes 1.365 but votes for S/R/H (erasing I), and L32 N32:1117 delivers the strongest I-specific signal at 1.176 projection.

deep_dives.label: Structural writer L32:H18
deep_dives.caption: The single strongest attention writing event: L32:H18 contributes 1.98 projection by reading structural contacts (50.3% structural attention). This head integrates the buried hydrophobic environment into the final I prediction.

deep_dives.label: Final prediction channels L33
deep_dives.caption: The dominant I-specific features that cement the prediction. F33:5788 (MLP, 117.27 proj) and F33:4166 (attn, 106.12 proj) are highly enriched for isoleucine and represent the model's strongest evidence for beta-branching specificity at this position.

equation_narrative.resolution: The model correctly predicts isoleucine by assembling a representation of position 3's buried hydrophobic core environment through structural contacts, then activating beta-branching-specific prediction channels in layers 28-33. The strongest evidence comes from L32-L33: MLP neuron N32:1117 (1.176 proj), structural attention L32:H18 (1.98 proj reading buried contacts), and final-layer feature F33:5788 (117.27 proj) all encode isoleucine's specific geometry. The model distinguishes I from the chemically similar valine and leucine through late-layer features that capture beta-branching specificity, achieving 74.72% confidence in a context where all three branched-chain aliphatics are structurally plausible.
